The Bank of Japan will sell tomorrow 200billion yen in financing bills through 35-day repurchaseagreements maturing July 24 to help mop up a projected moneymarket surplus, money traders said.    The yield on the bills for sale to banks and securitieshouses from money houses will be 3.6005 against today'sone-month commercial bill discount rate of 3.5625 pct andone-month certificate of deposit rate of 3.98/86 pct. Tradersestimate a 300 billion yen surplus due to tax allocations tolocal governments and public entities. The operation will putoutstanding bill supplies at about 2,000 billion yen. REUTER&#3;